	Meeting a self-imposed deadline of this week to resolve questions he himself raised by implying that he had taped Mr. Comey, Mr. Trump said on Twitter that he had not made tapes of what Mr. Comey has testified were attempts by the president to derail the Justice Department’s investigation.

	...Mr. Trump’s original tweet appeared to refer to an article in The New York Times that reported that he had asked Mr. Comey to pledge loyalty during a dinner at the White House shortly after the inauguration.


Trump came out swinging with threats he could blackmail Comey with the tapes. But after he denied asking for Comey's loyalty in an interview with Jeanine Pirro, Trump didn't sound so confident. It sounds like Trump was lying about the loyalty question.


Trump claims his meeting with Lavrov was "very public," but he announced it with less than 24 hours warning and barred the U.S. press from attending:


